    s1_title:       "Step 1 — Key Normalization",
    s1_explain:     "The HMAC algorithm requires the key to be exactly 64 bytes long (the SHA-256 block size = 512 bits). <strong>If the key is shorter than 64 bytes</strong>, it is padded with zero bytes (0x00) on the right. <strong>If the key is longer than 64 bytes</strong>, it is first hashed with SHA-256, producing 32 bytes, which are then padded to 64 bytes.",
    s1_orig:        "🔑 Original Key Bytes",
    s1_padded:      "📦 Padded to 64 bytes",
    s1_info_pre:    "Key length: ",
