    s2_title:       "Step 2 — XOR with ipad (Inner Padding)",
    s2_explain:     "ipad = 0x36 (binary: 00110110) repeated 64 times. We XOR every byte of the padded key K' with 0x36. This XOR operation 'mixes' the key with a fixed constant, creating a unique inner key. The result K'⊕ipad is then concatenated with the message before the first hash.",
    s2_kp:          "K' (padded key)",
    s2_ipad:        "⊕ ipad (0x36 × 64)",
    s2_res:         "= K' ⊕ ipad result",

    s3_title:       "Step 3 — Inner Hash (First SHA-256)",
    s3_explain:     "Concatenate the result of (K'⊕ipad) with the message, then apply SHA-256. This binds the message to the key. Even if an attacker knows the message, they cannot compute this hash without knowing K'⊕ipad (which requires the secret key).",
    s3_input:       "Input to SHA-256:",
