    s3_output:      "⬇️ SHA-256 Output (Inner Hash):",

    s4_title:       "Step 4 — XOR with opad (Outer Padding)",
    s4_explain:     "opad = 0x5C (binary: 01011100) repeated 64 times. We XOR the same padded key K' with 0x5C. Note that opad and ipad differ in every bit position — this mathematical property ensures the inner and outer keys are completely different, preventing related-key attacks.",
    s4_kp:          "K' (padded key)",
    s4_opad:        "⊕ opad (0x5C × 64)",
    s4_res:         "= K' ⊕ opad result",

    s5_title:       "Step 5 — Outer Hash (Final HMAC)",
